habitat_description:
Zalophus californianus occupies rocky shores (Gonzalez-Suarez and Gerber, 2008; French et al., 2011) and open, flat beaches (DeLong and Melin, 2000; Garcia-Aguilar et al., 2013). The species is also known to haulout on jetties, logbooms, docks, and buoys (Jeffries et al., 2000).

After summer breeding along California and Mexico (DeLong and Melin, 2000; Zenier et al., 1990), males often migrate to the northwest, while females and pups generally remain in the south (Antonelis and Fiscus, 1980; Jeffries et al., 2000).
